<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>A top women's rugby player awarded the MBE for her services to the sport made hoax 999 calls and waved a knife at police, a court heard.</p>

<p>Non Evans, 46, broke records when she became the first woman to compete in three sports at the Commonwealth Games.</p>

<p>But she spiralled into 'attention seeking' behaviour after leaving sports left 'a huge hole' in her life.</p>

<p>Swansea Magistrates' Court heard Evans (pictured with her MBE) brandished the knife at officers and grabbed their body-worn cameras to offer cash to 'keep quiet</p>

<p>A court heard Evans made 'rambling calls' to the Welsh Ambulance Service reporting somebody unable to breathe.</p>

<p>She also launched a tirade of abuse at a neighbour before waving a kitchen knife in the road.</p>

<p>Police were called to her house in Swansea, South Wales, on August 25.</p>

<p>Swansea Magistrates' Court heard Evans brandished the knife at officers and grabbed their body-worn cameras to offer cash to 'keep quiet.'</p>

<p>She told officers she was 'attention seeking' and admitted to drinking half a bottle of vodka.</p>

<p>Evans pleaded guilty to threatening behaviour and sending communications conveying false information.</p>

<p>Swansea Magistrates' Court heard Evans launched a tirade of abuse at a neighbour before waving a kitchen knife in the road</p>

<p>Defending Stuart John said she was 'lost' and was struggling to come to terms with retirement from international sports.</p>

<p>He said it had left 'a huge hole' in her life causing her depression, anxiety and alcohol misuse.  </p>

<p>Her problems were also made worse in lockdown because she has been unable to attend face-to-face counselling sessions, the court was told.</p>

<p>Evans was given a nine week sentence, suspended for 12 months.</p>

<p>Evans was awarded the MBE in the 2011 Birthday Honours for services to sport - the first ever female rugby player to receive the award</p>

<p>She also given a 20-day rehabilitation order and ordered to pay a total of £213 in court costs.</p>

<p>The sportswoman previously represented Wales in rugby, judo, weightlifting and wrestling over her impressive career.</p>

<p>She was awarded the MBE in the 2011 Birthday Honours for services to sport - the first ever female rugby player to receive the award.     </p>

<p>In a highly emotional series of Tweets, Evans revealed in  July that she is gay. </p>

<p>The confessional post read: 'Please don't judge me I am gay. Sorry it took me 30 years to say that.</p>

<p>'I have always wanted to tell the world that I'm gay. But I didn't want to upset my parents x'.</p>

<p>Her revelation was met with an outpouring of support from fans and other sports stars online. </p>

<p> </p>

<p>.</p>
